In a large saucepan, saute bell pepper, onion and garlic in oil, stirring occasionally until onion is soft, about 6 minutes. Add rice vinegar, herbs, salt and pepper; cook 1 minute. Stir in broth and currants; bring to a boil. Stir in couscous and spinach; cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes; fluff couscous lightly with a fork.